text: Bernhard Hiesinger (born 27 April 1947) is a German rower who represented West Germany. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City with the men's coxless pair where they came twelfth. ==References== Category:1947 births Category:Living people Category:German male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of West Germany Category:Rowers at the 1968 Summer Olympics Category:People from Albstadt
